      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Abuse of Heroin, All Around</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Abraham G White letter on Apr 25 article urges steps to prevent heroin abuse by suburban teenagers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Prevention of heroin abuse is not discussed in your article about heroin use among suburban teenagers (''Face of Heroin: It's Younger and Suburban,'' news article, April 25).</p>
        <p>Psychological stress associated with emotional disturbances like anger, depression and anxiety are significant pathogenic factors in heroin addiction.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Prevention of heroin abuse is not discussed in your article about heroin use among suburban teenagers (''Face of Heroin: It's Younger and Suburban,'' news article, April 25).</p>
        <p>Psychological stress associated with emotional disturbances like anger, depression and anxiety are significant pathogenic factors in heroin addiction.</p>
        <p>Early recognition of the psychological disturbances by family, friends and teachers, and subsequent treatment can play an important preventive role.</p>
        <p>ABRAHAM  G. WHITE , M.D.  Forest Hills, Queens, April 25, 2000</p>
      </block>
